This dish is so delicious, we think it could inspire proposals, plus it's quick and easy
to boot—ready in just 20 minutes! The sauce is a combo of sun-dried tomatoes, cream
cheese, chicken stock, garlic, butter, and chiles. It's rich and creamy, but with a
bright, addictive sun-dried tomato tang. It's draped over juicy seared chicken and
tender penne.

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Finely chop
@sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%oz}.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain and
set aside.

Open package of @chicken breast{10%oz}(chopped) and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken
and scallion whites; season with half the @dried thyme{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

When chicken has about 30 seconds left, stir in @garlic powder{1%tsp} and as many
@chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like.

Add @tomato paste{1} to pan with chicken mixture. Cook, stirring, until coated and
slightly darkened in color, ~{30%seconds}.

Add 1/2 cup water, sun-dried tomatoes, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @cream cheese{4%tbsp},
and @butter{2%tbsp}. Cook, stirring and scraping up any browned bits from bottom of
pan, until thoroughly combined, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add drained pasta to pan with sauce; toss to coat. Taste and season with salt and
pepper if desired.

> TIP: If needed, add pasta cooking water a splash at a time until everything is
> coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between shallow #bowls{}; garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.